SIMPLE: spavin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spavin
<hw>Spav"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>spaveyne</ets>, OF. <ets>esparvain</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧parvin</ets>; akin to OF. <ets>espervier</ets> a sparrow
hawk, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧pervier</ets>, fr. OHG. <ets>sparw⟦amac⟧ri</ets>
(G. <ets>sperber</ets>), fr. OHG. <ets>sparo</ets> sparrow, because this
disease makes the horse raise the infirm leg in the manner of a sparrow
hawk or sparrow. See <er>Sparrow</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A
disease of horses characterized by a bony swelling developed on the hock
as the result of inflammation of the bones; also, the swelling itself.
The resulting lameness is due to the inflammation, and not the bony
tumor as popularly supposed.</def> <rj><au>Harbaugh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bog spavin</b></col>, <cd>a soft swelling produced by
distention of the capsular ligament of the hock; -- called also
<altname>blood spavin</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Bone spavin</b></col>,
<cd>spavin attended with exostosis; ordinary spavin.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spavined</ent>⟦br⟧
